snippet: The plan to leave the Golan Heights followed reports that Croatia was selling weapons to Saudi Arabia that were being funneled to Syrian rebels.
abstract: Croatian Prime Min Zoran Milanovic says his country will withdraw its soldiers from United Nations peacekeeping force in the Golan Heights after reports that Croatia is selling weapons that are being funneled to antigovernment fighters in Syria.
lead_paragraph: The plan to leave the Golan Heights followed reports that Croatia was selling weapons to Saudi Arabia that were being funneled to Syrian rebels.
